com.inqwell.any.client

Class AnyDocument

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractComposite
      • com.inqwell.any.AbstractMap
        • com.inqwell.any.client.AnyDocument
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, AnyPrintable, Composite, Map, Vectored, Serializable

    public class AnyDocument
extends AbstractMap
implements Map, Vectored, AnyPrintable
    Subsume a Swing text document into the Inq environment. This class wraps an instance of javax.swing.text.Document providing access to it and its element content via Inq node references and acting as the required type for document operations.

    Although a map, it does not contain anything in its own right. Because it represents a Document, which has only a root node, the mutation methods are not supported and the 'Map' only contains one element known as 'root'.

    This class also manages the styles that are used and supports static methods for returning a style based on the given attributes.

    See Also:
    AnyElement, Serialized Form

      • addByVector

        public void addByVector(int at,
                        Any value)
        Description copied from interface: Vectored
        Places the given value at the specified location in the collection. If the location is not in the range 0 to entries() then an exception is generated unless the collection can be sparse. If setSparse(true) has previously been called then place-holders are inserted as required.

        If the implementation is a map then a suitable key will be invented for the value, for example its identity.

        Specified by:
        addByVector in interface Vectored

        public static MutableAttributeSet getStyle(Any a)

      • getString

        public static String getString(Any a)
                        throws AnyException
        Get the string to be rendered. The argument may be an instance of AnyIcon, StringI or Map. If it is a Map then the map should contain the well-known keys and values for style content.

        As required by DefaultStyledDocument, this method returns a single space for Icons.

        Throws:
        AnyException

      • getRenderStyle

        public static MutableAttributeSet getRenderStyle(Map item)
                                          throws AnyException
        Create new style to render the given item. The map is processed and the items within it that are keyed by the well-known values for style elements are converted to the appropriate type.

        Care should be taken with the map as all items will be placed in the style. Those that are not recognised as style items are placed in the style as is. This is useful for storing auxiliary information in the style that is required later, for example the URL reference in hyperlink text.

        Throws:
        AnyException
